statements.name: PROC PRINTTO
statements.description: Defines destinations, other than ODS destinations, for SAS procedure output and for the SAS log.

arguments.name: LABEL=
arguments.description: provides a description for a SAS log or procedure output stored in a SAS catalog entry.

arguments.name: LOG=
arguments.description: routes the SAS log to a permanent external file or SAS catalog entry.

arguments.name: LOG
arguments.description: routes the SAS log to its default destination.

arguments.name: 'external-file'
arguments.description: the name of an external file specified in quotation marks.

arguments.name: log-filename
arguments.description: is an unquoted alphanumeric text string. SAS creates a log that uses log-filename.log as the log filename.

arguments.name: fileref
arguments.description: a fileref previously assigned to an external file.

arguments.name: <.LOG>
arguments.description: a SAS catalog entry stored in the SAS library and SAS catalog specified.

arguments.name: fileref
arguments.description: a fileref previously assigned to a SAS catalog entry. See .

arguments.name: NEW
arguments.description: replaces the file instead of appending to it.

arguments.name: PRINT=
arguments.description: routes procedure output to a permanent external file or SAS catalog entry or printer.

arguments.name: PRINT
arguments.description: routes procedure output to its default destination.

arguments.name: 'external-file'
arguments.description: the name of an external file specified in quotation marks.

arguments.name: print-filename
arguments.description: is an unquoted alphanumeric text string. SAS creates a print file that uses print-filename as the print filename.

arguments.name: fileref
arguments.description: a fileref previously assigned to an external file.

arguments.name: <.OUTPUT>
arguments.description: a SAS catalog entry stored in the SAS library and SAS catalog specified.

arguments.name: fileref
arguments.description: a fileref previously assigned to a SAS catalog entry. See .

arguments.name: UNIT=
arguments.description: routes the output to the file identified by the fileref.
